I changed the terms 'north Indian' and 'south Indian', as these were not distinctions that existed 1400 years ago. Furthermore, the armies of both the Chalukyas and Gurjara-Pratiharas fought in Western and North-western India and were pan-Indian entities. It is factually inaccurate to attach loosely defined terms like 'north Indian' and 'south Indian', especially in the first paragraph of the page itself. There were also a few grammatical errors that were rectified.
